HEADWORD: Predilection
<hw>Pre`di*lec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>pre-</ets> + L. <ets>dilectus</ets>, p. p. <ets>diligere</ets> to
prefer: cf. F. <ets>pr⟦eacute⟧dilection</ets>. See
<er>Diligent</er>.]</ety> <def>A previous liking; a prepossession of
mind in favor of something; predisposition to choose or like;
partiality.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

